#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:14
msgid ""
"In previous lessons, we decreased and increased a character's health, but "
"there was no limit to how much health they could have."
msgstr ""
"En las lecciones anteriores, disminuimos y aumentamos la salud de un "
"personaje, pero no había límite para la cantidad de salud que este podía "
"tener."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:34
msgid ""
"As a result, the player could increase their character's health "
"indefinitely, which we do not want."
msgstr ""
"Como resultado, el jugador podía aumentar la salud de su personaje "
"indefinidamente, lo cual no queremos."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:52
msgid "What happens to health when we damage our character?"
msgstr "¿Qué ocurre con la salud cuando dañamos a nuestro personaje?"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:53
msgid ""
"Suppose our character has [code]100[/code] health.\n"
"\n"
"What would the value of health be if we called [code]take_damage(25)[/code] "
"[b]five times[/b]?"
msgstr ""
"Supongamos que nuestro personaje tiene [code]100[/code] de salud.\n"
"\n"
"¿Cuál sería el valor de la salud si llamáramos a [code]take_damage(25)[/"
"code] [b]cinco veces[/b]?"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:57
msgid ""
"Calling [code]take_damage(25)[/code] five times would subtract a total of "
"[code]125[/code] from [code]100[/code].\n"
"\n"
"100\n"
"75\n"
"50\n"
"25\n"
"0\n"
"-25"
msgstr ""
"Llamar a [code]take_damage(25)[/code] cinco veces restaría un total de "
"[code]125[/code] a [code]100[/code].\n"
"\n"
"100\n"
"75\n"
"50\n"
"25\n"
"0\n"
"-25"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:65
#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:66
msgid "-25"
msgstr "-25"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:65
msgid "25"
msgstr "25"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:65
msgid "0"
msgstr "0"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:75
msgid ""
"We can use conditions to run actions [b]selectively[/b].\n"
"\n"
"Conditions make your code branch into two paths: if the condition is met, "
"the computer will run the corresponding instructions. Otherwise, those "
"instructions will not run at all."
msgstr ""
"Podemos usar condiciones para ejecutar acciones [b]selectivamente[/b].\n"
"\n"
"Las condiciones hacen que tu código se ramifique en dos caminos: si la "
"condición se cumple, la computadora ejecutará las instrucciones "
"correspondientes. De lo contrario, esas instrucciones no se ejecutarán."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:87
msgid ""
"Video games and other computer programs are full of conditions. For example, "
"game input largely relies on conditions: [i]if[/i] the player presses the "
"button on a gamepad, the character jumps."
msgstr ""
"Los videojuegos y otros programas informáticos están llenos de condiciones. "
"Por ejemplo, la entrada del juego depende en gran medida de las condiciones: "
"[i]si[/i] el jugador presiona el botón de un gamepad, el personaje salta."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:107
msgid ""
"When the computer checks a condition, this is called [b]to evaluate[/b] a "
"condition. All conditions [b]evaluate[/b] to either [code]true[/code] or "
"[code]false[/code].\n"
"\n"
"Either the player is pressing the button, or not. Either the character is "
"touching an enemy, or not. \n"
"\n"
"In our case, [i]if[/i] the health goes over a maximum value, we want to "
"reset it to the maximum.\n"
"\n"
"To define a condition, we use the [code]if[/code] keyword. We write a line "
"starting with [code]if[/code], type the condition to evaluate, and end the "
"line with a colon."
msgstr ""
"Cuando la computadora verifica una condición, esto se llama [b]evaluar[/b] "
"una condición. Todas las condiciones [b]se evalúan[/b] como [code]true[/"
"code] o como [code]false[/code].\n"
"\n"
"O el jugador está pulsando el botón, o no. O el personaje está tocando a un "
"enemigo, o no\n"
"\n"
"En nuestro caso, [i]si[/i] la salud supera un valor máximo, queremos "
"restablecerla a dicho valor máximo.\n"
"\n"
"Para definir una condición, utilizamos la palabra clave [code]if[/code]. "
"Escribimos una línea que empiece con [code]if[/code], escribimos la "
"condición que se debe evaluar y terminamos la línea con dos puntos."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:133
msgid ""
"Notice the [code]>[/code] comparison sign. We read this symbol as \"greater "
"than\". \n"
"\n"
"We've seen how function definitions use a colon at the end of the first line "
"and nest content inside.\n"
"\n"
"In GDScript, this syntax is a recurring pattern for all code blocks.\n"
"\n"
"The computer knows which instructions belong to the condition because they "
"are indented."
msgstr ""
"Observa el signo de comparación [code]>[/code]. Este símbolo se lee como "
"\"mayor que\".\n"
"\n"
"Hemos visto cómo las definiciones de funciones utilizan dos puntos al final "
"de la primera línea y anidan el contenido en su interior.\n"
"\n"
"En GDScript, esta sintaxis es un patrón recurrente para todos los bloques de "
"código.\n"
"\n"
"La computadora sabe qué instrucciones pertenecen a la condición porque "
"tienen sangría."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:157
msgid "Comparisons"
msgstr "Comparaciones"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:159
msgid ""
"In the above example, we used the [code]>[/code] syntax to mean \"greater "
"than\".\n"
"\n"
"We can compare numbers in other ways too.\n"
"\n"
"[code]>[/code] means \"greater than\"\n"
"[code]<[/code] means \"less than\"\n"
"[code]==[/code] means \"equal to\"\n"
"[code]!=[/code] means \"not equal to\"\n"
"\n"
"Here's how we might use these in [code]if[/code] statements.\n"
msgstr ""
"En el ejemplo anterior, usamos la sintaxis [code]>[/code] para designar "
"\"mayor que\".\n"
"\n"
"También podemos comparar números de otras formas.\n"
"\n"
"[code]>[/code] significa \"mayor que\"\n"
"[code]<[/code] significa \"menor que\"\n"
"[code]==[/code] significa \"igual a\"\n"
"[code]=[/code] significa \"no igual a\"\n"
"\n"
"Así es como podríamos utilizarlos en las declaraciones [code]if[/code].\n"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:187
msgid "Which of these statements are true?"
msgstr "¿Cuál de estas afirmaciones es cierta?"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:190
msgid ""
"The comparison [code]3 > 1[/code] means \"three is greater than one\" which "
"is [b]true[/b].\n"
"The comparison [code]2 < 3[/code] means \"two is less than three\" which is "
"[b]true[/b].\n"
"The comparison [code]1 != 3[/code] means \"one is not equal to three\" which "
"is [b]true[/b].\n"
"\n"
"The comparison [code]2 == 1[/code] means \"two is equal to one\" which is "
"[b]false[/b].\n"
"The comparison [code]3 < 1[/code] means \"three is less than one\" which is "
"[b]false[/b]."
msgstr ""
"La comparación [code]3 > 1[/code] significa \"tres es mayor que uno\", lo "
"cual es [b]verdadero[/b].\n"
"La comparación [code]2 < 3[/code] significa \"dos es menor que tres\", lo "
"cual es [b]verdadero[/b].\n"
"La comparación [code]1 != 3[/code] significa \"uno no es igual a tres\", lo "
"cual es [b]verdadero[/b].\n"
"\n"
"La comparación [code]2 == 1[/code] significa \"dos es igual a uno\", lo cual "
"es [b]falso[/b].\n"
"La comparación [code]3 < 1[/code] significa \"tres es menor que uno\", lo "
"cual es [b]falso[/b]."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:196
#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:197
msgid "3 > 1"
msgstr "3 > 1"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:196
msgid "2 == 1"
msgstr "2 == 1"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:196
#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:197
msgid "2 < 3"
msgstr "2 < 3"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:196
#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:197
msgid "1 != 3"
msgstr "1 != 3"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:196
msgid "3 < 1"
msgstr "3 < 1"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:204
msgid "Or else..."
msgstr "Si no..."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:206
msgid ""
"The [code]if[/code] keyword comes with a complementary [code]else[/code] "
"keyword.\n"
"\n"
"You can write an [code]else[/code] block after an [code]if[/code] block, "
"like so."
msgstr ""
"La palabra clave [code]if[/code] viene acompañada de una palabra clave "
"complementaria [code]else[/code], que significa \"si no\".\n"
"\n"
"Puedes escribir un bloque [code]else[/code] después de un bloque [code]if[/"
"code], así."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:228
msgid ""
"The [code]else[/code] block will run whenever the condition above it isn't "
"met."
msgstr ""
"El bloque [code]else[/code] se ejecutará siempre que no se cumpla la "
"condición anterior a él."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:238
msgid ""
"In the following practices, we'll use conditions and improve the way our "
"character's health changes so it has limits."
msgstr ""
"En las siguientes prácticas, utilizaremos condiciones y mejoraremos la forma "
"en que cambia la salud de nuestro personaje para que tenga límites."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:246
msgid "Using Comparisons"
msgstr "Usar comparaciones"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:247
msgid ""
"This series of [code]if[/code] statements is all wrong. Change the "
"comparisons so each comparison matches the instruction below it.\n"
"\n"
"Keep the values and statements as they are; only change the comparison "
"signs.\n"
"\n"
"As a reminder, the comparison signs are:\n"
"[code]\n"
"> greater than\n"
"< less than\n"
"== equal to\n"
"!= not equal to\n"
"[/code]\n"
"\n"
"The line [code]health < 5:[/code] means \"health is less than 5\". \n"
"\n"
"Because [code]health = 100[/code], this is false so [code]print(\"health is "
"greater than five.\")[/code] won't run."
msgstr ""
"Esta serie de sentencias [code]if[/code] está incorrecta. Cambia las "
"comparaciones para que cada una de ellas coincida con la instrucción que "
"está debajo de ella.\n"
"\n"
"Mantén los valores y las sentencias como están; sólo cambia los signos de "
"comparación.\n"
"\n"
"Como recordatorio, los signos de comparación son:\n"
"[code]\n"
"> mayor que\n"
"< menor que\n"
"== igual a\n"
"!= no igual a\n"
"[/code]\n"
"\n"
"La línea [code]health < 5:[/code] significa \"la salud es inferior a 5\"\n"
"\n"
"Debido a que [code]health = 100[/code], esto es falso, por lo que "
"[code]print(\"health is greater than five.\")[/code] no se ejecutará."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:283
msgid ""
"Comparing values allows us to make decisions in code. But there's something "
"wrong with these statements.."
msgstr ""
"Comparar valores nos permite tomar decisiones en el código. Pero hay algo "
"mal en estas sentencias..."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:288
msgid "Limiting Healing"
msgstr "Limitar la curación"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:289
msgid ""
"We have a heal function that adds an amount to the character's health.\n"
"\n"
"Add to the function so the character's health is never greater than "
"[code]80[/code]."
msgstr ""
"Tenemos una función de curación que agrega una cantidad a la salud del "
"personaje.\n"
"\n"
"Agrega código a la función para que la salud del personaje nunca sea mayor "
"que [code]80[/code]."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:301
msgid ""
"As much as we might like, we don't want our robot to have too much health. "
"Limit how much healing the robot can take."
msgstr ""
"Por mucho que nos guste la idea, no queremos que nuestro robot tenga "
"demasiada salud. Limita la cantidad de curación que puede recibir el robot."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:306
msgid "Preventing Health from Going Below Zero"
msgstr "Evitar que la salud caiga por debajo de cero"

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:307
msgid ""
"When the robot takes damage, its health can be negative.\n"
"\n"
"We might want to display the health number on screen, like in Japanese "
"RPGs.\n"
"\n"
"We don't want negative numbers. We want to stop at zero instead.\n"
"\n"
"Calling the function should reduce [code]health[/code] by [code]amount[/"
"code].\n"
"\n"
"If [code]health[/code] goes below [code]0[/code], set it to [code]0[/code] "
"again."
msgstr ""
"Cuando el robot recibe daño, su salud puede ser negativa.\n"
"\n"
"Puede que queramos mostrar el número de salud en la pantalla, como en los "
"RPGs japoneses.\n"
"\n"
"No queremos números negativos. En su lugar, queremos detenernos en cero.\n"
"\n"
"Llamar a la función debería reducir [code]health[/code] por [code]amount[/"
"code].\n"
"\n"
"Si la [code]health[/code] cae por debajo de [code]0[/code], ponla de nuevo "
"en [code]0[/code]."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:325
msgid ""
"Having a negative health value doesn't make a lot of sense. Make sure the "
"robot's health can't go below zero."
msgstr ""
"Tener un valor de salud negativo no tiene mucho sentido. Asegúrate de que la "
"salud del robot no pueda bajar de cero."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.tres:329
msgid "Conditions"
msgstr "Condiciones"
